        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "8fd553b5-57ee-4d6d-a5e6-4c7d9da15db0",
      "name": "Check incomplete cap",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [
        1472,
        608
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const item = $input.first().json;\n\n// Read incompleteRunIndex from Incomplete counter (if it executed)\nlet incompleteCount = 0;\ntry {\n  if ($('Incomplete counter').isExecuted) {\n    incompleteCount = Number($('Incomplete counter').last().json.incompleteRunIndex) || 0;\n  }\n} catch {}\n\n// totalTraversals from Run counter\nlet totalTraversals = 0;\ntry {\n  totalTraversals = Number($('Run counter').last().json.runIndex) || 0;\n} catch {}\n\nconst questionCount = Math.max(0, totalTraversals - incompleteCount);\n\n// Read accumulatedOutcomes from staticData\nconst staticData = $getWorkflowStaticData('global');\nconst key = $execution.id;\nconst accumulatedOutcomes = (staticData[key] ? [...staticData[key]] : []);\n// Clean up staticData for this execution to prevent unbounded growth\ndelete staticData[key];\n\n// Determine if this is a failure\nlet error = item.error;\n// On the cap-exhausted path, Notify cap (HTTP Request) replaces the payload\n// with its response, so error set by Output (cap exhausted) is lost. Pull from source.\ntry {\n  if (!error && $('Output (cap exhausted)').isExecuted) {\n    error = $('Output (cap exhausted)').last().json.error;\n  }\n} catch {}\nconst outcome = item.outcome;\nif (outcome === 'UNKNOWN' && !error) {\n  error = { message: 'outcome classified as UNKNOWN' };\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: {\n  ...item,\n  incompleteCount,\n  questionCount,\n  outcomeHistory: accumulatedOutcomes,\n  accumulatedOutcomes,\n  error,\n}}];"
      },
      "id": "9c4a7026-80ea-47d4-85ec-edb753d733d7",
      "name": "Compute counts",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1264,
        96
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const stdout = String($input.first().json.stdout ?? '');\nlet sessionId = null;\nlet sessionIdMissing = false;\n\n// Scan all stdout lines for first JSON with .sessionID\nconst lines = stdout.split('\\n').filter(l => l.trim());\nfor (const line of lines) {\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(line);\n    if (parsed && parsed.sessionID) {\n      sessionId = parsed.sessionID;\n      break;\n    }\n  } catch {}\n}\n\nif (!sessionId) {\n  sessionIdMissing = true;\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: { ...$input.first().json, sessionId, sessionIdMissing } }];"
      },
      "id": "08d73969-57bd-4a8a-9395-381896dc3709",
      "name": "Extract SessionID",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        432,
        16
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7a158182-4f88-432d-b820-e39d69bd0699",
      "name": "Note: INCOMPLETE path overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        950,
        -80
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "content": "# INCOMPLETE outcome classification\n\nopencode sessions can quit mid-stream (timeout, provider error, truncation) and are resumable. Previously these were misclassified as QUESTION, stalling the pipeline on a human form for hours.\n\n**4-rule routing:**\n- COMPLETE → output (success)\n- QUESTION → human form\n- INCOMPLETE → auto-continue (resume with \"Continue\", up to `incompleteContinueCap`, then fail)\n- UNKNOWN → fail (retries via existing machinery)\n\nINCOMPLETE re-enters at `Agent run (follow-up)` (uses `--session <id>`), bypassing the Get response Wait form entirely.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 500
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "cdca3b8a-ebd7-469d-b8e0-759b9c00a0f3",
      "name": "Note: Bug 2 fix — error assignment",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1600,
        800
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 5,
        "content": "# Bug 2 fix: error assignment\n\nPreviously set no `error` field, so `Assess step result` (`failed = item.error !== undefined`) treated cap-exhaustion as success.\n\nFix: explicit `error` assignment. Chose this over `includeOtherFields: true` to keep the Output schema fixed at 8 fields for the Develop Story journal contract.",
        "height": 200,
        "width": 350
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "93d2548f-d0b5-49cf-b9e2-52c25b5adb09",
      "name": "Note: Compute counts rationale",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1450,
        -50
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "content": "# Compute counts — branch-local counters\n\nDerives counts from branch-local `$runIndex` counters, not the shared Run counter spine:\n- `incompleteCount` = Incomplete counter's `$runIndex` (INCOMPLETE branch only)\n- `questionCount` = totalTraversals − incompleteTraversals\n\nUsing the shared spine for both would pollute `questionCount` — an INCOMPLETE-continue would count as a human-form halt (false autonomy signal).\n\nAlso cleans up `$getWorkflowStaticData('global')` entry keyed by `$execution.id`. If this node doesn't run (crash/cancel), the entry leaks — static data is never auto-deleted.",
        "height": 250,
        "width": 400
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5e555249-da8e-498e-a46c-14e361e45bae",
      "name": "Note: Accrete outcome rationale",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        850,
        380
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "content": "# Accrete outcome — static data across Wait\n\nUses `$getWorkflowStaticData` because `$('BMAD Outcome').all()` does not aggregate across the Get response Wait-node resume boundary. Without this, mid-stream INCOMPLETE/QUESTION outcomes vanish from `outcomeHistory` and reflection sees only the final outcome.\n\nBoth Accrete nodes key on `$execution.id` and push to `staticData[key]`. Cleanup happens in Compute counts.",
        "height": 220,
        "width": 350
      }
    }
  ],
